FT  31 JUL 93 / Children lead Welsh speakers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE HIGHEST proportion of Welsh speakers is found among children, the 1992
Welsh social survey found. A third can speak the language, compared with
21.5 per cent of the overall Welsh population.
There are estimated to be 368,000 fluent Welsh speakers and another 95,000
people who can speak a fair amount.
