<HEADLINE>
FT  31 JUL 93 / UK, France agree to join forces to persuade EC to change the
Acquired Rights Directive 1977
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE UK and France have agreed to join forces in persuading the European
Community to change the Acquired Rights Directive 1977. Implementation of
the directive in the UK through the Tupe regulations has created uncertainty
over its application when public services are contracted out.
The French government is believed to be concerned about the impact of the
directive on its plans to privatise state-owned banks and industries.
At Monday's summit meeting, Mr John Major, the prime minister, and Mr
Francois Mitterrand, the French president, agreed to include the directive
in 24 items of EC legislation they wish to be reviewed.
</TEXT>
