<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JUL 93 / International Capital Markets: NZ futures market to link
with Sydney
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE New Zealand Futures &amp; Options Exchange, acquired by Sydney Futures
Exchange last year, is to link its computerised futures market with the
Australian market, AP-DJ reports from Wellington.
Plans will now proceed to allow trading on New Zealand futures contracts in
Australia. The link is expected to increase liquidity in local futures
trading. A survey of Sydney exchange members shows that between 15 and 20 of
them planned to link with the New Zealand exchange.
Mr Les Hosking, chief executive of the Sydney exchange, said extra liquidity
from Australia and further afield would help the New Zealand financial
market use futures and options on futures to manage risk.
</TEXT>
