FT  30 JUL 93 / International Company News: McCaw narrows deficit to Dollars
22.1m in second period
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MCCAW Cellular Commun-ications, the largest cellular telecoms company in the
US, yesterday announced a narrowing in second-quarter losses to Dollars
22.1m, as net revenues from cellular operations climbed 28 per cent to
Dollars 313.6m. In the same quarter a year ago, McCaw incurred a restated
loss of Dollars 65.8m.
The fast-growing, heavily indebted business said that cellular subscriptions
continued to grow strongly in the quarter, rising 31 per cent to 2.5m by the
end of June. The increase boosted cashflow 32 per cent to Dollars 189m, and
was achieved in spite of a well-publicised health scare about the use of
cellular phones.
Mr Craig McCaw, chairman and chief executive, said that while current
opportunities in the cellular business were unparalleled, there were further
investments in the technology to be made.
LIN Broadcasting, another cellular telecommunications company that is
majority-owned by McCaw, also announced growth in cashflow and subscribers
yesterday. Net revenues in the quarter rose 22 per cent to Dollars 185.4m,
and cash flow from cellular operations climbed 21 per cent to Dollars 90.4m.
Like McCaw, LIN carries a heavy debt load, and net losses in the quarter
totalled Dollars 16.6m, up from a Dollars 12.7m loss a year ago.
</TEXT>
