FT  30 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Ex-Lands offer and placing to raise Pounds
15m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER, Property Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EX-LANDS, a property inv-estment and management group, has announced a
placing and open offer to raise Pounds 15m.
It is also buying a Pounds 5.8m portfolio of property in South Kensington,
comprising 13,730 sq ft of offices, 13 retail units and nine flats.
The remainder of the funds will be available for further purchases of high
yielding property and additional working capital to fund the development of
golf courses in continental Europe.
Ex-Lands is managed by Mr Robert Bourne and Mr Graham Bourne, who used to
run Local London before it was sold to Priest Marians in 1989. The Saatchi
brothers, founders of the advertising group, own 10 per cent of the shares.
The offer entitles shareholders to apply for Pounds 1 nominal of 7.5 per
cent convertible unsecured loan stock 2020 for every five shares held. The
offer has been underwritten by Paribas.
The company said it expects to make a pre-tax profit for the year to June 30
1993 of at least Pounds 900,000. It intends to pay a dividend of 0.35p for
the year.
