The improvement was achieved on turnover up from Pounds 14m to Pounds 20.1m.
However, the company said the results were not comparable with those of
1992, primarily because of the inclusion of Spectrum Marketing and
Quickbond.
Earnings came out at 2.38p (1.49p) per share. The interim dividend is raised
to 1.1p (1p). The shares closed up 2p at 68p.
</TEXT>
