<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JUL 93 / Imperial Chemicals Industries
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Imperial Chemical Industries, yesterday reported its last set of results
including Zeneca, its bioscience business.
Shorn of Zeneca and its fibres operations, sold to Du Pont, first-half
profits before tax and exceptional items rose from Pounds 146m to Pounds
167m. Trading profits were up from Pounds 149m to Pounds 180m.
The results benefited from currency movements and cost savings. Mr Ronnie
Hampel, chief executive, said: 'I regard the performance as solid in very
difficult circumstances.' For many of the businesses, the trading
environment continued to be tough. It was essential to pursue restructuring
programmes vigorously.
