FT  30 JUL 93 / Concern at court funds fraud
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MORE THAN 50 cases of attempted or successful fraud involving about Pounds
1m in the Court Funds Office were uncovered between 1988 and 1992, a report
by the National Audit Office yesterday says.
The Court Funds Office, part of the Public Trust Office, administers and
manages funds deposited in the courts on behalf of minors and mental
patients and by suitors in litigation.
Systems and procedures have been reviewed and strengthened but because of
the complexity of the work and inability to identify the culprits 'there
remain some continuing unavoidable risks and concerns', the report says.
