FT  30 JUL 93 / VSEL
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
VSEL is being investigated for possible under-reporting of profits since
privatisation in 1986, the National Audit Office report reveals.
Under the privatisation agreement, if VSEL made pre-tax profits of more than
Pounds 90m in the six years after it was sold it would have to pay half the
extra to British Shipbuilders up to a limit of Pounds 40m.
After extraordinary items VSEL made Pounds 35.8m over the period, said the
NAO.
But it said a review by British Shipbuilders accountants' 'raises a
possibility that VSEL may be required to pay further consideration to
British Shipbuilders'.
